cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel multi-stage tracking framework that involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves object detection and localization, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Control) as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several benchmark datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
